wood Bowl]]\n| Concert Production\n|\n|-\n| 2017\n| rowspan=4| ''[[Waitress (musical)|Waitress]]''\n| rowspan=4| Jenna Hunterson\n| March 31 \u2013 June 11, 2017\n| rowspan=3| [[Brooks Atkinson Theatre]]\n| rowspan=3| [[Broadway theatre|Broadway]]\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web |first=Lindsay |last= Kimble |title='Sugar, Butter, Broadway': Sara Bareilles Taking Over the Lead Role in Her Musical Waitress |url=https://people.com/theater/sara-bareilles-starring-in-waitress-broadway/ |date=February 16, 2017 |work=People}}</ref>}}\n|-\n| 2018\n| January 16 \u2013 March 11, 2018\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web |first=Allison |last= Stubblebine |title=Sara Bareilles Returning to 'Waitress,' Joining Jason Mraz For Two Week Run |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/broadway/8053916/sara-bareilles-waitress-jason-mraz-two-week-run-january-2018 |date=November 29, 2017 |website=Billboard }}</ref>}}\n|-\n| 2019\n| January 7 \u2013 February 3, 2019\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web |first=Andrew |last= Gans |title=Sara Bareilles Will Return to Broadway's Waitress Opposite Tony Winner Gavin Creel |url=http://www.playbill.com/article/sara-bareilles-will-return-to-broadways-waitress-opposite-tony-winner-gavin-creel |date=December 7, 2018 |website=Playbill }}</ref>}}\n|-\n|-\n| 2020\n| January 27 \u2013 March 14, 2020\n| [[Adelphi Theatre]]\n| [[West End theatre|West End]]\n| {{center|<ref>{{cite web |first=Dan |last=Meyer |title=Sara Bareilles to Join Waitress in the West End Opposite Gavin Creel |url=http://www.playbill.com/article/sara-bareilles-to-join-waitress-in-the-west-end-opposite-gavin-creel |date=November 4, 2019 |website=Playbill }}</ref>}}\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%\" \n|-\n! Year\n! Association\n! Category\n! Nominated work\n! Result\n! {{Abbr|Ref.|Reference(s)}}\n|-\n|2008\n|[https://www.ascap.com/press/2008/0312_sara_bareilles.aspx ASCAP Pop Music Awards]\n|ASCAP Vanguard Award\n|Herself\n|{{won}}\n|{{center|<ref>{{C